  "strategy": [
    "Default to move_forward when path is clear and wall is present on the left.",
    "If obstacle_front is detected, escape by moving backward or performing a full scan.",
    "If obstacle_left is lost, rotate left (counterclockwise) to re-acquire the wall.",
    "If obstacle_right is detected (but not front), rotate left to avoid right-side collision.",
    "Commit states ensure atomic actions and prevent oscillations.",
    "Uncontrollable events are always handled first and are total for all states.",
    "No state enables both rotate directions or both move_forward and move_backward, except obs_front for robust escape.",
    "After recovery (move_backward), perform a scan to reorient before resuming wall-following.",
    "Transitions are deterministic and avoid infinite controllable loops."
  ]
